Text: Victory! After weeks of striking, the graduate UAW student workers with @SW_Columbia have won a fair contract. The power of the labor movement is strong and growing. I was so proud to stand with these student workers.

Tonight, I stood alongside @SpeakerPelosi to lead members of the Senate and House in a prayer vigil one year after January 6th.

We remembered the bravery of those who defended our Capitol and those who worked in our Capitol.

We reflected on how we will act to protect democracy. https://t.co/SCk8qh4Lum

One year ago—we saw something from those insurrectionists I’ve been told has never happened before:

The Confederate flag waved inside the U.S. Capitol.

These searing, un-American images are solemn reminders we must act to protect democracy.

https://t.co/n2fRBIrhaN

Thank you to President Biden @POTUS and Vice President Harris @VP for coming to the Capitol to address the nation on the January 6th insurrection anniversary

This day is a reminder that attacks on our democracy are ongoing

We will act to protect our democracy and voting rights https://t.co/KeLi2UboIP

I just spoke with @SecretaryPete who told me the 2nd Ave Subway is moving into what @FTA_DOT calls its engineering phase.

What that means:

We're one step closer to securing billions in federal grants, and bringing 2nd Ave Subway equity to the people of East Harlem.

After President Biden’s address to the nation today, Donald Trump did it again—lying about the election.

It was Donald Trump’s Big Lie that soaked our political landscape in kerosene.

We must confront this Big Lie. We will move forward to protect democracy and voting rights. https://t.co/vM0jkuU6Uw

Billy Evans of MA

Gunther Hashida of VA

Howie Liebengood of VA

We remember our emergency responders who have died in the days and months after January 6th. We mourn their loss. We honor their limitless heroism.

We honor the workers in the Capitol on January 6th—those who've lost their lives, those who protected the Capitol, those who had to hide from the insurrectionists, those who made sure the count went forward, those who had to clean up afterwards, those who had to repair the damage

What I just said in the Senate on the January 6th anniversary:

The attack didn’t come out of the blue

It was an attempt to reverse our election

Violent insurrection—Call it what it is!

It was spurred by Trump’s Big Lie, still with us now

We will act to protect our democracy

Today, we mark the anniversary of January 6th

We remember thanks to the bravery of our Capitol Police we moved forward with counting the ballots

And we know the root cause of January 6th is still with us—Trump’s Big Lie

We will move forward to protect democracy & voting rights https://t.co/hAXGDyWSjs

The root cause of January 6th is still with us today

It lives on through Trump's Big Lie that's undermining faith in our political system and making our democracy less safe

The Senate will take action to move forward on legislation to protect our democracy and the right to vote https://t.co/jLwY3uEXQf

Unless we confront Trump’s Big Lie

Unless we fortify and strengthen our democracy

The political violence of January 6 risks becoming little more than a taste of dangers to come.

We will take action to move forward on legislation to protect our democracy and the right to vote. https://t.co/dDTT3OW4nQ

I spoke at today's Rules Committee hearing on protecting our Capitol after the January 6 insurrection

Because the root cause of the violent assault on our transfer of power is still making our democracy less safe—Trump's Big Lie

We will move forward to protect the right to vote https://t.co/GJGsmmyErO

I remember January 6th like it was yesterday. I was within 30 feet of the insurrectionists.

But thanks to bravery of our Capitol Police—we moved forward with counting the ballots

We've taken action since to protect the Capitol

Now we will move forward to protect our democracy https://t.co/ojdT7p6K7I

As we near the January 6 anniversary, threats of political violence are on the rise

And unless we confront Trump's Big Lie, January 6 risks becoming little more than a taste of dangers to come

The Senate will move forward to protect our democracy and safeguard the right to vote

January 6th wasn't merely a senseless act of mob violence.

It was a violent attempt to reverse our election.

The root cause: Trump’s Big Lie that continues to make our democracy less safe.

The Senate will move forward to protect our democracy and cure America of the Big Lie.

A far-right leader dismantling democracy

That's who Trump endorsed so close to the anniversary of the Jan. 6 insurrection spurred by his Big Lie

That's where Trump wants America to go

We can’t let it happen

The Senate will act to support our democracy & protect voting rights https://t.co/d7G4BKNcTJ
Millions of Americans need relief. President Biden can #CancelStudentDebt today. https://t.co/jCZdxnSSMB

The War on Drugs has been a war on people—particularly people of color

I'm working to pass our bill to end the federal marijuana prohibition, enact criminal justice reforms, and ensure equity for those impacted by the War on Drugs.

If Republicans continue to hijack the rules of the Senate to prevent action on protecting our democracy:
 
We will debate and consider changes to the rules on or before January 17, Martin Luther king Jr. Day.

The stakes could not be higher. We will move forward.

The January 6th insurrection. New voter restriction laws. The state-level efforts to subvert democracy.

All manifestations of Trump’s Big Lie.

We can and must take strong action to stop this anti-democratic march.

The Senate is going to move forward. https://t.co/MBCKKq6C2v

If Republicans continue to block our efforts,

The Senate will debate and consider changes to Senate rules on or before January 17, Martin Luther King Jr. Day, to protect the foundation of our democracy:

Free and fair elections.

Let me be clear: January 6th was a symptom of a broader illness, an effort to delegitimize our election process, and the Senate must advance systemic reforms to repair our democracy or else the events of that day will not be an aberration—they will be the new norm.

Make no mistake: This week, @SenateDems will make clear what happened on January 6th is directly linked to the one-sided, partisan actions being taken by GOP-led state legislatures across the country. We can and must take strong action to stop this anti-democratic march. https://t.co/tLkpfObZAS

On January 12th, Senator Harry Reid will lie in state in the United States Capitol Rotunda.

It will be an honor to pay tribute to him in the Capitol next week.

I’m praying for her family and her loved ones. And we will keep working to make our streets safer from traffic violence.

In honor of former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid:

He’s gone but will walk by the sides of many of us in the Senate every day https://t.co/8T9PiD7vY4

With @POTUS’s signing into law our bill to transform research into ALS:

Today would be a great day for a follow-up announcement that he's going to #CancelStudentDebt!

Today, President Biden is signing the ACT for ALS Act we passed in the Senate into law.

It's historic legislation.

It will transform research into ALS.

It will spur the discovery of new treatments and cures for ALS patients.

I’m proud to have fought for it.

We got this done.

I have filed cloture to start the process on more than 20 of President Biden’s nominees.

I was proud to recommend her to @POTUS for the Eastern District of New York and am ecstatic he's nominated her to the federal bench.

I recommended Hector Gonzalez, Nina Morrison, and Jessica Clarke as federal judges in New York.

I'm thrilled @POTUS has nominated them.
